Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has described the Gauteng education system as an elephant that carries itself &amp; leads in many respects. DAVEYTON - Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has described the Gauteng education system as an elephant that carries itself and leads in many respects.Motshekga attended a ceremony to celebrate the province's results and its top achieving pupils in Daveyton on the East Rand.Gauteng achieved an 87% pass rate, the third highest achieving province in the country.Basic Education Minister Angie Motshekga has commended MEC Panyaza Lesufi and the results that Gauteng achieved during the 2016 academic year.Motshekga says she believes Gauteng has managed to get through a number of challenges, where other provinces haven t. Gauteng is an elephant that carries itself with utmost dignity, because other elephants are not coping, namely KwaZulu-Natal. Gauteng is an elephant that s running with springboks. Motshekga says Gauteng also leads in a number of respects, like providing access to education for special needs pupils.Lesufi is determined to increase the pass rate in the province this year to at least 90%.To get your 2016 matric results go to EWN s special matric results page. Share the page with your friends.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)